    <name>
				<text>(not in quiz) 37.2.3.11 Seven batches of articles are manufactured</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p><p>Seven batches of articles are manufactured. Each batch contains {@n_art_each_batch@} articles. Each article has, independently, a probability of {@p_art_being_def@} of being defective. Find the probability that there is at least one defective article:</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>In exactly 4 of the batches [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p>In 4 or more of the batches [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>

</ol>
<p><b>Note:</b> round your answer up to \(4\) decimal places.</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p><b>SOLUTION:</b></p><p>First, let's compute the probability of having at least 1 defective article on each batch:</p><p>Let \(Z\) be the number of defective articles in a batch, this follows a binomial distribution with \(n={@n_art_each_batch@}\) and \(p = {@p_art_being_def@} \)</p><p>\(\begin{align} \text{P}(Z \geq 1) &amp; = 1 - \text{P}(Z &lt; 1) = 1 - \text{P}(Z=0) \\ &amp; = 1 - \ ^{@n_art_each_batch@}\!C_0p^0(1-p)^{{@n_art_each_batch@}} = 1 - (1 - {@p_art_being_def@})^{{@n_art_each_batch@}} \approx {@p_batch@}&nbsp;\end{align}&nbsp;\)</p><p>With the latter result, we can compute now what the exercise is asking us. Let \(X\) be the number of batches with at least one defective article, so \(X\) follows a binomial distribution with \(n = 7\) and \(p = {@p_batch@}\):</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>\(\text{P} (X=4) =&nbsp;\ ^7\!C_4({@p_batch@})^4(1-{{@p_batch@}})^3 = {@ta_1@}&nbsp; \)</p></li>

<li><p>\(\begin{align} \text{P} (X\geq 4)&nbsp; = &amp; \ ^7\!C_4({@p_batch@})^4(1-{{@p_batch@}})^3 +&nbsp;^7\!C_5({@p_batch@})^5(1-{{@p_batch@}})^2 \\ &amp; +&nbsp;^7\!C_6({@p_batch@})^6(1-{{@p_batch@}}) +&nbsp;^7\!C_7({@p_batch@})^7&nbsp;= {@ta_2@}&nbsp;\end{align} \)</p></li>

</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
